(1)

1622 Richmond Road, at the S. E. corner of Liberty Avenue, showing the Egbert House. It was the house of Joseph Egbert, Congressman for one term, and County Clerk for one year in 1869. It is a Colonial dwelling. The view is north.

P. L. Sperr
Winter, 1925

(2)

The same, looking south.

P. L. Sperr
Winter, 1925

(3)

The rear of the Egbert House.

P. L. Sperr
1924
